entry.name: NAS-MIB|system info|system uptime
entry.description: The amount of time since this host was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime in the SNMPv2-MIB [RFC1907] because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

entry.name: NAS-MIB|system info|if number
entry.description: The number of network interfaces (regardless of their current state) present on this system.

entry.name: NAS-MIB|system if: #[1.3.6.1.4.1.24681.1.2.9.1.1]|if index
entry.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of IfNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

entry.name: NAS-MIB|system if: #[1.3.6.1.4.1.24681.1.2.9.1.1]|if descr
entry.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the hardware interface.
